{"info": {"author": "Jarik Marwede", "author_email": "jarikmarwede@zoho.eu", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# Center tk window\nA small library for centering tkinter windows on their parent or on the screen.\n\n## Installation\nTo install run the following command:\n`pip install center_tk_window`\n\n## Usage\n```python\nimport tkinter\nimport center_tk_window\n\nroot_window = tkinter.Tk()\nwindow_to_center = tkinter.Toplevel(root_window)\n\n# Center a window on its parent unless it is the root window in which case it will be centered on screen.\ncenter_tk_window.center(root_window, window_to_center)\n\n# Center a window on its parent\ncenter_tk_window.center_on_parent(root_window, window_to_center)\n\n# Center a window on the screen\ncenter_tk_window.center_on_screen(window_to_center)\n\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/jarikmarwede/center-tk-window", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "center-tk-window", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/center-tk-window/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/center-tk-window/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/jarikmarwede/center-tk-window"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/center-tk-window/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Functions for centering tkinter windows on parent or on screen", "version": "1.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Center tk window</h1>\n<p>A small library for centering tkinter windows on their parent or on the screen.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>To install run the following command:\n<code>pip install center_tk_window</code></p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">tkinter</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">center_tk_window</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">root_window</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">tkinter</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tk</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"n\">window_to_center</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">tkinter</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Toplevel</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">root_window</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Center a window on its parent unless it is the root window in which case it will be centered on screen.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">center_tk_window</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">center</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">root_window</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">window_to_center</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Center a window on its parent</span>\n<span class=\"n\">center_tk_window</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">center_on_parent</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">root_window</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">window_to_center</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Center a window on the screen</span>\n<span class=\"n\">center_tk_window</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">center_on_screen</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">window_to_center</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 5491159, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "0539c8eced71e9fd898140f581d9a768", "sha256": "5f4ca4e20b3ba2ded93accafc3f21c2d32baedeb2b562ed5d2deecf6db397651"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "center_tk_window-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md